author: Ayodele Oluwagbemi
title: PHOTOS: Again, group protests against Amnesty International in Abuja
text:
Tweet 
A group of protesters on Wednesday took to the streets of Abuja, condemning the activities of Amnesty International in Nigeria. 
This is the second protest by the group, Global Peace and Rescue Initiative. They had on Monday barricaded the Abuja office of the Amnesty International and gave the body a 24-hour ultimatum to quit the country. 
Here are photos of the latest protest. 
Photos: Olatunji Obasa.
